          <TD align=right>
            <div align="center">
              <center>
              <table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    &nbsp;
                  </td>
              </center>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    
                    <p><font face="Verdana" color="#A80000"><b>Event: State Delegate Assembly
                    </b></font></p>
                    <p><font face="Arial" size="2">  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt">For
  the ninth year, the WASC Governing Board has scheduled the required <b> State
  Delegate Assembly (SDA</b>) as a separate meeting.&nbsp; Previously it had been held in
  conjunction with the State Conference. Since we now have two, scheduling it at
  one of the State Conferences could be unfair to one segment of the membership
  or the other. Furthermore, the Long Range Planning Committee and the Governing
  Board believes that the &quot;business of the Association&quot; should be very
  important to the membership. Thus, the SDA should be scheduled as a separate
  program permitting ample time to thoroughly discuss and ultimately reach
  decisions on all agenda items.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Specifics
  for the 2000-01 State Delegate Assembly are as follows:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>Date: Monday, April 2, 2001</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt"><img border="1" src="http://www.wasc.org/images/capital.jpg" align="right" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="138" height="162"><b>Site:
  State Capitol Assembly Chambers</b></p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt">Schedule:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
  </span>9:30 AM Registration</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>10:00 AM Call to Order</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>10:15 AM Speaker</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>10:45 AM Business Meeting</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>1:00 PM Anticipated Adjournment!</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>FEE:
  $10.00/School + $2.00/Delegate</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt">Minutes
  of the 2000 SDA, potential 2001-2002 resolutions and state projects, an agenda
  and other details for the 2000 SDA will be mailed to all member schools prior
  to March 2<sup>nd</sup>, 30 days prior to the event as required by the
  Association By-Laws.</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt">Regions
  have the option of scheduling their spring business meeting on Sunday, April
  1, at the Madison Concourse Hotel, the day before the SDA. Region IV is the
  only region<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>that has scheduled
  their meeting for this date and site. A mailing from the region at a later
  date will specify further details.</p>
  <p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 0in 220.5pt">The
  following WASC By-Laws relate to the SDA:</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 4.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -4.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 220.5pt"><b>ARTICLE
  VI SECTION A.<o:p>
  </o:p>
  </b></p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 4.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -4.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">5.
  <b><u>State Delegate Assembly</u></b>.</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 13.5pt left 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1">a.<span style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>The State Delegate Assembly shall be comprised of the<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
  </span>two voting delegates from each regular member organization.</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list .25in left 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1">b.<span style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>Governing Board members shall also be voting delegates<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
  </span>to the delegate assembly.</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 4.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -4.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in"><b>ARTICLE
  XI SECTION B.<o:p>
  </o:p>
  </b></p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">3.
  b.<span style="mso-tab-count: 1"> </span><b><u>State Delegate Assembly</u></b>.
  There shall be a Delegate Assembly held each spring at a site and time
  determined by the Governing Board. The State Conference and Delegate Assembly
  may be held concurrently. It shall be the function of the State Delegate
  Assembly to consider and act upon:</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">(1)
  Old and new business.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>(2)
  Proposed Resolutions and State Projects. (3) Proposed amendments to the
  By&#8209;Laws.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>(4) And other
  agenda items.</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 4.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -4.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">4.
  <b><u>State Caucuses</u></b>.</p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: 13.5pt list .5in left 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo2">a.<span style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>An opportunity shall be provided for Advisor and<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
  </span>Student Caucuses as part of the State Delegate Assembly. Caucuses shall
  be composed of all<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>voting
  representatives at the State Delegate – student and adult representatives
  may caucus separately.<o:p>
  </o:p>
  </p>
  <p style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list .5in left 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo2">b.<span style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span>It shall be the purpose of
  the State Caucuses to:</p>
  <p style="tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">(1) Review the
  agenda and conduct hearings on business to come before the State Delegate
  Assembly.</p>
  <p style="tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">(2) Provide the
  opportunity to formulate items of new business.</p>
  <p style="tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in">&nbsp;</p>
  <p style="tab-stops: 220.5pt 3.75in 4.0in" align="left"><b>Although
  member schools have only two votes, additional representatives are welcome to
  attend the meeting.<o:p>
  </o:p>
  </b></p>

                    </font></p>
                    <p align="right"><i>&nbsp;
